'''Mobile Telecommunication Company of Esfahan''' (شرکت مخابرات سیار اصفهان, '''MTCE''') also known as '''Espadan''' was a [[mobile network operator]] in Iran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=8511728|title=Mobile Telecommunications Company of Esfahan: Private Company Information - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ihs.com/country-industry-forecasting.html?ID=106599432|title=Iran to License Third Nationwide Cellular Operator|website=www.ihs.com|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref>

Following the agreements reached during the Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani's visit to Malaysia in 1994, and according to the laws of attracting and supporting foreign investment, in 29 May 2001 the license for launching the first [[Prepay mobile phone|prepaid mobile telephone]] network in Iran with an initial capacity of 20 thousand subscribers was granted to [[Celcom]] for 15 years, and the Malaysian Technology Resources Industry Company received permission to use [[GSM]] 24.18 Mbit/s bandwidth within the [[Isfahan]] province.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mtce.ir/contactus/about-us.dot|title=درباره ما - MTCE|date=2016-04-02|access-date=2017-11-25|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402164244/http://mtce.ir/contactus/about-us.dot|archivedate=2016-04-02|df=}}</ref>

In 2005 Celcom sold its stakes to [[Telekom Malaysia|TM International(Telekom Malaysia).]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2011/12/13/axiata-plans-to-offload-iranian-unit-to-unknown-party/|title=Axiata plans to offload Iranian unit to unknown party|last=TeleGeography|website=www.telegeography.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2010/12/29/axiata-sells-samart-stake-may-offload-iranian-telco-shares/|title=Axiata sells Samart stake, may offload Iranian telco shares|last=TeleGeography|website=www.telegeography.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2007/10/02/cellphones-outnumber-fixed-lines-in-iran/|title=Cellphones outnumber fixed lines in Iran|last=TeleGeography|website=www.telegeography.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2005/05/26/millicom-leads-the-pack-as-competition-belatedly-arrives-in-iran-mobile-market/|title=Millicom leads the pack as competition belatedly arrives in Iran mobile market|last=TeleGeography|website=www.telegeography.com|language=en|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref>

In 2008 MTCE bought the [[WiMAX]] license from '''Iranian Communications Regulatory Authority''' (CRA).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2013/06/25/only-four-companies-licensed-to-offer-wimax-in-iran/|title=Only four companies licensed to offer WiMAX in Iran|last=TeleGeography|website=www.telegeography.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref>

In 2011 MTCE went broke and deactivated all sim cards following merger with [[Mobile Telecommunication Company of Iran|Mobile Telecommunications Company of Iran]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tcz.ir/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=461:espadan&catid=64:newsarchives&Itemid=155|title=آخرین وضعیت ادغام شبکه اسپادان با مخابرات ایران   {{!}} پورتال شرکت مخابرات منطقه زنجان|last=عمومی|first=روابط|website=tcz.ir|language=fa-ir|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mehrnews.com/news/1297364/%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1%DB%8C%D9%86-%D9%88%D8%B6%D8%B9%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%BA%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B4%D8%A8%DA%A9%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%BE%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%85%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%B8%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%AF%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%AA|title=آخرین وضعیت ادغام شبکه اسپادان با مخابرات ایران/ در انتظار دریافت مجوز کتبی|date=2011-05-03|work=خبرگزاری مهر {{!}} اخبار ایران و جهان {{!}} Mehr News Agency|access-date=2017-11-25|language=fa}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://donya-e-eqtesad.com/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AC%DB%8C%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%84-19/401106-%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%AA%D8%B1%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%AE%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%AF-%D9%86%D9%88%D8%B9-%D8%B3%DB%8C%D9%85-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%A8-%DA%A9%D9%86%D9%86%D8%AF|title=مشترکان مختارند نوع سیم‌کارتشان را انتخاب کنند|work=روزنامه دنیای اقتصاد|access-date=2017-11-25|language=fa}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tct.ir/?siteid=5&pageid=352&newsview=48327|title=مخابرات از نگاه مطبوعات - اخبار > مدیرعامل شرکت مخابرات ایران خبر داد انحلال یا ادغام 30 شرکت‌ مخابرات استانی/ بلاتکلیفی محل تامین هزینه‌ هم‌کدی|website=www.tct.ir|access-date=2017-11-25}}</ref>

