A '''theory of operation''' is a description of how a [[tool|device]] or [[system]] should work.  It is often included in [[documentation]], especially [[maintenance, repair and operations|maintenance/service]] documentation, or a [[user manual]].  It aids [[troubleshooting]] by providing the troubleshooter with a [[mental model]] of how the system is supposed to work.  The troubleshooter can then more easily identify discrepancies, to aid [[diagnosis]] of problem.

IBM Redbooks<ref name=IBM>
{{cite book |url=http://www.redbooks.ibm.com/Redbooks.nsf/pages/redbooks?Open |title=About IBM Redbooks |publisher=IBM |accessdate=November 11, 2011}}</ref> are "Theories of operation" of their products.

